      • dictionary

        ITransducerBuilder dictionary(Collection<String> dictionary)

        Parameters:
        dictionary - Collection of dictionary terms to consider when generating spelling candidates.
        Returns:
        This ITransducerBuilder or an equivalent one, for fluency.

        isSorted - Whether the dictionary is sorted. If it is not sorted then it will probably be sorted.

      • defaultMaxDistance

        ITransducerBuilder defaultMaxDistance(int defaultMaxDistance)
        Specifies the default, maximum tolerated error of spelling candidates from the query term. This value is used if the transducer is called without explicitly specifying the maximum distance. It default to infinity, which will return every term in the dictionary, so if you plan on using the implicit maximum distance then you should set it here.
        Parameters:
        defaultMaxDistance - Default, maximum tolerated errors between spelling candidates and the query term.
        Returns:
        This ITransducerBuilder or an equivalent one, for fluency.

      • includeDistance

        ITransducerBuilder includeDistance(boolean includeDistance)
        Specifies whether the distance between each spelling candidate and the query term should be returned with the spelling candidate.
        Parameters:
        includeDistance - Whether to include distances with spelling candidates.
        Returns:
        This ITransducerBuilder or an equivalent one, for fluency.

      • maxCandidates

        ITransducerBuilder maxCandidates(int maxCandidates)
        If you only desire a subset of the spelling candidates for a query term, you may specify the number of candidates to return, here. Note that the candidates are not guaranteed to be ordered such that you would get the nearest candidates in the collection if you limit its size.
        Parameters:
        maxCandidates - Maximum number of candidates to include in the collections of spelling candidates.
        Returns:
        This ITransducerBuilder or an equivalent one, for fluency.

      • build

        <CandidateType> ITransducer<CandidateType> build()
        Builds a Levenshtein transducer according to the parameters set for this ITransducerBuilder.
        Type Parameters:
        CandidateType - Implicit type of the spelling candidates generated by the transducer.
        Returns:
        Levenshtein transducer for seeking spelling candidates for query terms (fuzzy searching!).
